HEADWORD: Ciliata
<hw>Cil`i*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Cilia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the orders of
Infusoria, characterized by having cilia. In some species the cilia
cover the body generally, in others they form a band around the
mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

